           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-CT (01/20)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 2 of 4</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
			
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block>
			c.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The following definition is added:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			• 
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Termination of Coverage</fo:inline> means, whether made by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at any time: (1) cancellation or nonrenewal of this
			policy; or (2) decrease in the Limit of Liability, reduction of
			coverage, increased Deductible, new exclusion, or any other change in
			coverage less favorable to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			5.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm" >
			Section VI., General Condition D., Cancellation and Nonrenewal, is deleted and replaced with the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
		 	D.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Nonrenewal, Conditional Renewal, Premium Billing, Cancellation, and History Report and Claim Information
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			1.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold">
			Nonrenewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not refuse to renew this policy, unless the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			or its agent sends, by registered or certified mail or by mail
			evidenced by a certificate of mailing, or delivers to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the address shown in the policy, at least 90 days’ advance
			notice of its intention not to renew. The notice of intent not to renew
			shall state or be accompanied by a statement specifying the reason for
			such nonrenewal.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			This subsection shall not apply:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			in case of nonpayment of premium;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
				if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> fails to pay any advance premium required by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> for renewal; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(c)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			if this policy is transferred from the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> to an affiliate of
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> for another policy with no interruption of coverage and
			contains the same terms, conditions and provisions, including policy
			limits, as the transferred policy, except that the insurer to which the
			policy is transferred shall not be prohibited from applying its rates
			and rating plans at the time of renewal.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			2.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Conditional Renewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> intends to renew this policy, but under terms or
			conditions less favorable than previously provided, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> must
			notify the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> by sending a conditional renewal notice. The
			conditional renewal notice must clearly state or be accompanied by a
			clear statement that identifies terms or conditions that may be less
			favorable to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> under the ensuing policy such as:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			an increase in the Deductible
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			a decrease in the Limit of Liability; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(c)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			a new exclusion or deletion of coverage.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not conditionally renew this policy, unless the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its agent sends, by registered or certified mail or by mail
			evidenced by a certificate of mailing, or delivers to the Named
			Insured, at the address shown in the policy, at least 90 days’ advance
			notice of its intention to conditionally renew.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			3.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold">
			Premium Billing
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			A premium billing notice shall be mailed or delivered to the 
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its agent not less than 30 days in advance of
			the renewal date of this policy. Such notice shall not be required if
			the premium for the ensuing policy period is to increase less than 10%
			on an annual basis. The premium billing notice shall be based on the
			rates and rules applicable to the ensuing policy period and shall
			include a notice of transfer when the policy has been transferred form
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> to an affiliate of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> pursuant to subsection 1.(c)
			above. The provisions of this subsection shall not apply if the if the
			annual premium for this policy is $50,000 or more.
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block start-indent="14mm">
			Failure of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its agent to provide the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> with
			the required notice of nonrenewal, conditional renewal or premium
			billing shall entitle the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> to: (i) renewal of the policy
			for a term of not less than one year; and (ii) the privilege of
			pro-rata cancellation at the lower of the current or previous year
			rates if exercised by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> within 60 days from the renewal
			date. Renewal of a policy shall not constitute a waiver or estoppel
			with respect to grounds for cancellation which existed before the
			effective date of such renewal.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			4.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			Cancellation
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block margin-top="2cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-CT (01/20)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 3 of 4</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
		
		<fo:list-block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may cancel this policy at any time prior to the
			expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> by providing prior written notice
			to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or by surrender of this policy to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its
			authorized agent. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			shall return 90% of the unearned portion of the premium.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may only cancel this policy for nonpayment of premium.
			This policy may be canceled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing or delivering to
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the address shown in the policy, written notice
			of cancellation at least 90 days before the effective date of
			cancellation. The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may continue the coverage and avoid the
			effect of the cancellation by payment in full at any time prior to the
			effective date of cancellation. No notice of cancellation shall be
			effective unless it is sent, by registered or certified mail or by mail
			evidenced by a U.S. Post Office certificate of mailing, or delivered by
			the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> by the required date. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall credit the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> the pro
			rata unearned portion of the premium. Payment or tender of any unearned
			premium by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not be a condition precedent to the
			effectiveness of cancellation, but such payment shall be made as soon
			as practicable.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			5.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			History Report and Claim Information
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			If this policy is nonrenewed or canceled for any reason by the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> or by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall furnish the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
			Insured</fo:inline> with written reports for the insured portion of the period
			beginning four years prior to the nonrenewal or cancellation date and
			ending six months prior to that date. Such reports shall include the
			following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			each policy number;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			each period of coverage provided;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(3)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			evidence that the reports are furnished by the Insurer;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(4)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			written premiums;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(5)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			pricing information and modifications used if requested by the Named Insured; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(6)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			a detailed listing of incurred losses.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			Such reports shall be provided not later than 30 days after receipt of
			the written request from the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> or its authorized producer.
			If subsequent reports updating the required information are needed to
			properly rate or to obtain insurance coverage with a different insurer,
			such reports shall be furnished by the prior insurer not later than 30
			days after receipt of a written request from the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> or its
			authorized producer.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall provide, not later than 30 days after receipt of
			a written request by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, a summary of policy claim
			information for a period commencing not more than four years prior to
			the date of the request. Such information shall include the following:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			each policy number;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			each period of coverage;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(3)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			the number of claims;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(4)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			the paid losses of all loss information; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(5)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			the date of each loss.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		<fo:block>
		All other terms, conditions and limitations of the policy remain unaltered.
